        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 8:48PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 848 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sylvania, or 7 miles northwest of Troy, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chemung, Southport, Sayre, Waverly, Athens, Ridgebury, Troy,
Springfield, South Waverly, and Wellsburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
